The Rutgers men's golf team hosted its third annual Johnnie-O tournament, with senior Noah Kumar shining as he finished in second place overall, shooting seven under par. His standout performance included a five under second round, where he maintained par or better on 17 of 18 holes. Coach Rob Shutte recognized Kumar's focus and confidence throughout the tournament, attributed to his previous experience at the venue. Despite challenges like high winds and a canceled third round, the team showed promise, with three additional players finishing in the top 50.
